kunyomiExamples.meaning: to groan, to moan, to roar, to howl, to growl, to hum (engine, wind, etc.), to buzz, to whiz, to sough, to make a low, dull sound, to ooh and aah (in admiration), to sing in a strong, low voice (esp. traditional chant or recitation), to be about to burst, to overflow
to a great extent, incredibly (tasty, much, etc.), (money) to burn, rolling in (cash)
groan, moan, growl, snarl, roar, howl, bellow, hum (e.g. of a motor), buzz, drone, wiz, device attached to a kite that makes a humming sound when the kite is flown, beat (acoustic interference)
groan, moan, growl, roar, snarl, hum (of a machine, power lines, etc.), drone (e.g. of an engine), buzz, howl (of the wind)
